JMPD spokesperson Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar. Twitter/@JoburgMPD JOHANNESBURG - After 41 years, JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar is retiring. He was joined by colleagues in Johannesburg to celebrate the event. Public safety MMC David Tembe and Johannesburg Mayor Mpho Phalatse were among them. During the farewell event, the mayor described Minnaar as passionate and honest. Minnaar joined law enforcement in 1981 as a traffic officer and rose to the official spokesperson in 2001. After 41 years of Golden Service, today we bid farewell to #JMPD Spokesperson Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar. We are joined by EM @mphophalatse1, MMC @David_S_Tembe # MMC @MichaelSun168
